{
  "stem": "5911.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So there was only one sister left, [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Chava. ?] She was still at university.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they all were university educated.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All very, very educated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my father too, very educated.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, my-- he wanted to-- not to go back to Lithuania, to Kovna.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the story goes that my-- my grandmother said that she lost her teeth worrying about my father.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was the only son.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he returned to Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He traveled to Paris.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He traveled-- I remember all the stories telling me all the adventures he had in Spain.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was a very interesting man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he introduced me in the-- to have the love of books.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We used to spend hours together.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My biggest thrill was in my father's store looking through books.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was from, as far as I can remember, '39 to '41 being with him all the time, being like his best friend, because like when the Russians came in 1940, it wasn't in style anymore to have like a governess or a  maid.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You see, they also took over the store.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "International bookstore.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father, Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They spoke Lithuanian and Russian too, because, you see, I still remember the Russian language, because-- actually speaking, because from the governess, that was my first language introduced into Russian.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Traditional, not Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It means that on the holidays, they went to shul.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember going with him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother was always working.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Her-- nursing was her life.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother's name is Batia Chaimovitz, maiden name Chaimovitz, and my-- and Schmidt.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And now it's Malamud-- M-A-L-A-M-U-D.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as far as I can remember, she was the Jewish General in-- a surgical nurse.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
